review_blob: Draught at Rocking Hearts in Uji. Alcohol taste at the back and not too sweet for a nice balance. Crisp and refreshing, and a nice change pace.

user_location: of Tadgs Irish Bar and Restaurant Japan
review_blob: Can (!) from Michaels in Kyoto. Very nice. Sweet aroma and very crisp. Good balance of malts and hops. I would love to try on draught.

user_location: of Tadgs Irish Bar and Restaurant Japan
review_blob: Draught at Kamikaze. Fairly light smokey aroma compared to Fujizakura. Very smooth and perfectly balanced. The sweetness at the beginning and smoke finishing it off were wonderful. It definitely does not feel like 7.5%.

user_location: of Tadgs Irish Bar and Restaurant Japan
review_blob: Can from Michaels on Kita-Shirakawa in Kyoto. Very nice and light. Kind of surprising for a brown ale. Perfect for the hot weather right. Nice sweet ending. It is nothing really exceptional, but it is very enjoyable (and quite inexpensive).

user_location: of Tadgs Irish Bar and Restaurant Japan
review_blob: Draught at Tadgs and Qbrick. Fruity nose. Really dry and sweet. But to me, never annoying. I taste strong vanilla and I like it. This is my perfect compliment as a second beer after an Imperial IPA in my lowly opinion.

user_location: of Tadgs Irish Bar and Restaurant Japan
review_blob: Draught at Devil Craft Tokyo. Its a great attempt at a scotch.really strong brown sugar. Sweet aroma. Just is too cloying compared to its rivals. Starts getting really annoying within the pint. First beer: half pinter.

review_blob: Draught at Ouef in Toyama. Really strong lemon smell, like a cleaning product. Sweet, but not too cloying. Kind of plain, but still nice.

review_blob: Draught at Tadgs Kyoto and Bungalo Kyoto for confirmation. Pleasant but weak aroma. Inescapable bite at the front. Really pleasant experience and an ideal first beer of the night. It wears on you as a drinking session goes forth.
